{"id":"d=origam-topic-4091//p=aa6a46ce7823454c9c525c2d8eb4c099","tags":{"__document_id":["origam-topic-4091"],"__file_type":["text/plain"],"__file_id":["0fff4ea393c2482c9a95cd7fe3cf4c0a"],"__file_part":["8180c0d3f2274cf6b5de92ae7115924f"],"__part_n":["0"],"__sect_n":["0"],"source":["origam-community"],"topicId":["4091"],"categoryId":["61"],"url":["https://community.origam.com/t/how-to-use-the-database-documentation-feature/4091"],"title":["How to use the database documentation feature"],"imagesFound":["3"],"imagesDescribed":["3"],"imageUrl":["https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/e/e537d1a4a8d20c0e72863ba30e8577a5e4751d68.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/7/74d6f20a31585efe2908a6ecd1694604cfd246f0.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/9/9c0fee3c78525672ec9a299f9d977116c47efee5.png"]},"payload":{"url":"","schema":"20231218A","file":"content.txt","text":"# How to use the database documentation feature\n\nURL: https://community.origam.com/t/how-to-use-the-database-documentation-feature/4091\n\n@vikter (2025-05-19 15:20:54Z):\n   \n This guide explains how to use the  Database Documentation generator . This  feature  was introduced in  version 2025.5 . \nTo use it, you must run both Architect and Server in version 2025.5 or newer. \nAdditionally, you must update your model by upgrading the system packages and adding the new package  Documentation . They are all available in the file  origam-model.zip  in the release assets. \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/e/e537d1a4a8d20c0e72863ba30e8577a5e4751d68.png]\nDescription: 2025.5.2 Pre-release documentation displaying the latest build information for version 2025.5.2.3860. Under \u0022Server Docker Images,\u0022 three command lines are provided for pulling Docker images: \u0022docker pull origam/server:2025.5.2.3860.linux,\u0022 \u0022docker pull origam/server:2025.5.2.3860.win-nano,\u0022 and \u0022docker pull origam/server:2025.5.2.3860.win-core.\u0022 A section labeled \u0022Assets\u0022 lists six downloadable files with their names, sizes, and last modified timestamps: \u0022origam-architect.msi\u0022 (10.2 MB, 29 minutes ago), \u0022origam-model.zip\u0022 (2.17 MB, 29 minutes ago), \u0022origam-scheduler.zip\u0022 (21.3 MB, 29 minutes ago), \u0022origam-server.zip\u0022 (36.3 MB, 29 minutes ago), and two source code options, both modified five days ago. A link to related change logs labeled \u0022HTML Chat\u0022 is also present.\n\n\n  \n   Documentation content \n This feature, located in a new package named  Documentation , provides a read-only screen with basic documentation of database table fields from all entities in all referenced and subordinate packages that contain entities. \n It displays only real database fields \u2014 no virtual fields, no functional fields, and no lookups. Only fields that physically exist in the database are shown. \n For each field, the following attributes are displayed: \n \n Caption \n Name \n AllowNulls \n DataType \n DataLength \n Entity name \n DefaultValue \n IsPrimaryKey \n ForeignKeyEntity \n ForeignKeyFiled \n Documentation fields \n \n   How to install \n To enable this feature in your project, activate the  Documentation  package by adding it to your project\u2019s package references: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/7/74d6f20a31585efe2908a6ecd1694604cfd246f0.png]\nDescription: The image displays a user interface for managing package references within a software application. The toolbar includes options labeled \u0022Add Reference\u0022 and \u0022Remove Reference\u0022 indicated by a plus sign and a minus sign, respectively. The section titled \u0022Referenced Package\u0022 features a list with two entries: \u0022Root Menu\u0022 and \u0022Documentation,\u0022 with \u0022Documentation\u0022 highlighted in red. The purpose of this interface is to enable users to manage and reference different packages in the application.\n\n\n  \n   How to use \n A user with permission to access this feature will find it in the client application under the main menu: \n Settings  /  Documentation  /  Database Field Description : \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/9/9c0fee3c78525672ec9a299f9d977116c47efee5.png]\nDescription: The interface displayed is from the Origam application, specifically the \u0022Database Field Description\u0022 section, which allows users to view and manage database fields\u0027 attributes. Visible UI elements include a navigation menu with options like \u0022Work Queue,\u0022 \u0022Favourites,\u0022 \u0022Menu,\u0022 \u0022Settings,\u0022 and \u0022Documentation.\u0022 The main grid presents a table with the following column headers: Package 1, Entity, Field Name, Caption, Allow Nulls, Data Type, Data Length, Default Value, Is Primary Key, Foreign Key Entity, Foreign Key Field, User Short Help, and User Long Help. Several rows of data show details about different fields such as \u0022Name,\u0022 \u0022Description,\u0022 and configuration options including \u0022Allow Nulls\u0022 and \u0022Data Type.\u0022 The apparent purpose of this interface is to facilitate the understanding and management of database fields for users working with the Origam data service.\n\n\n  \n By default, the screen displays all fields from your package, including those from referenced system packages such as  Root  or  Security . \nIf you want to view only the fields from specific packages, you can filter them accordingly.","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-05-01T23:56:35"},"vector":[-0.016839515,-0.019754134,-0.044042785,0.029267065,-0.032675683,-0.05665498,0.0390217,-0.006643376,0.00417778,0.008297957,-0.022577561,0.02510917,-0.0018756905,0.033089343,-0.010489227,0.007186354,-0.004863221,-0.006316959,0.023320636,0.03644829,-0.013061252,0.006605752,0.0438